NNoottiicceess
       There  are  minor  round  off  errors  when  adjusting the
       ranges, since PINT uses units of 1/1200 of  an  inch,  and
       SANE  normally  uses millimeters. Symptoms of these errors
       are skewed images. Use inches as the  scanning  unit,  and
       the scanner works correctly.

       The  PINT  0.5e interface does not provide a way to deter-
       mine valid ranges for DPI, modes, and scan sizes. The SANE
       backend queries the PINT device, and dynamically discovers

